<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 12:47:24 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>科学家首次恢复冷冻小鼠大脑的活动</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/scientists-revive-activity-in-frozen-mouse-brains-for-the-first-time</link><description>科幻小说中一个常见的比喻是冷冻保存的时间旅行者，他们的身体在假死状态下被深度冷冻，然后在下一个十年或一个世纪中解冻并重新唤醒，他们所有的精神和身体能力都完好无损。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-revive-activity-in-frozen-mouse-brains-for-the-first-time.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 12:47:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/scientists-revive-activity-in-frozen-mouse-brains-for-the-first-time</guid></item><item><title>微软实际上可能会让 Windows 11 变得更好，因为该公司承诺回滚人工智能功能并提高性能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/microsoft-might-actually-make-windows-11-good-as-the-company-promises-to-roll-back-ai-features-and-improve-performance</link><description>这些是我们一直在等待的更新。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/microsoft-might-actually-make-windows-11-good-as-the-company-promises-to-roll-back-ai-features-and-improve-performance.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 12:32:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/microsoft-might-actually-make-windows-11-good-as-the-company-promises-to-roll-back-ai-features-and-improve-performance</guid></item><item><title>行星大气的实验室版本</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/a-lab-version-of-planetary-atmospheres</link><description>研究人员在米大小的旋转圆柱体中重现了大气湍流的关键特征。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-lab-version-of-planetary-atmospheres.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 12:17:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/a-lab-version-of-planetary-atmospheres</guid></item><item><title>围堵干扰任意子</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/corralling-interfering-anyons</link><description>Link.aps.org/doi/10.1103/Physics.19。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/corralling-interfering-anyons.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 12:02:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/corralling-interfering-anyons</guid></item><item><title>紧凑型太赫兹成像系统使实时、非侵入性临床诊断更加接近</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/compact-terahertz-imaging-system-brings-real-time-non-invasive-clinical-diagnostics-closer</link><description>华威大学和埃克塞特大学的科学家开发了一种全光纤耦合的太赫兹（THz）成像系统，显着提高了太赫兹成像的速度、分辨率和临床实用性。该研究发表于&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/compact-terahertz-imaging-system-brings-real-time-non-invasive-clinical-diagnostics-closer.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 11:47:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/compact-terahertz-imaging-system-brings-real-time-non-invasive-clinical-diagnostics-closer</guid></item><item><title>电流稳定了新型计算不稳定点的自旋</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/electric-current-stabilizes-spins-at-unstable-points-for-new-types-of-computing</link><description>一个研究小组发现了一种利用电流控制材料内部微小磁性的新方法，这可能为新型计算技术铺平道路。这项工作基于自旋电子学，该领域不仅使用电子的电荷，还使用电子的“自旋”，这是一种可以被视为微小磁铁的量子特性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/electric-current-stabilizes-spins-at-unstable-points-for-new-types-of-computing.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 11:32:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/electric-current-stabilizes-spins-at-unstable-points-for-new-types-of-computing</guid></item><item><title>在氮化镓孔中观察到的首次量子振荡</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/first-quantum-oscillations-observed-in-gallium-nitride-holes</link><description>氮化镓是一种可以在高电压、高温度和高频率下工作的半导体，它使从 LED 照明到高功率电子产品的技术得以实现。现在，康奈尔大学的研究人员首次观察到该材料的量子特性，这一进步可能会扩大其技术范围。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/first-quantum-oscillations-observed-in-gallium-nitride-holes.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 11:17:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/first-quantum-oscillations-observed-in-gallium-nitride-holes</guid></item><item><title>霍尔“整流天线”可以检测 100 GHz 频率范围内的信号</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/a-hall-rectenna-can-detect-signals-over-a-100-ghz-frequency-range</link><description>当前的许多无线通信、成像和传感技术都依赖于将振荡电场和磁场（即电磁波）转换为电信号的组件。一些最常用的元件是所谓的 pn 二极管，这是一种结合了两种具有不同电气特性的材料的半导体器件。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-hall-rectenna-can-detect-signals-over-a-100-ghz-frequency-range2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 11:02:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/a-hall-rectenna-can-detect-signals-over-a-100-ghz-frequency-range</guid></item><item><title>超导交流磁体可以在不损失能量的情况下携带自旋</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/superconducting-altermagnets-could-carry-spin-without-energy-loss</link><description>研究人员提出，一种新发现的磁性材料可以将超导体的零电阻电流扩展到电子自旋。将他们的计算结果发表在&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/superconducting-altermagnets-could-carry-spin-without-energy-loss2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 10:47:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/superconducting-altermagnets-could-carry-spin-without-energy-loss</guid></item><item><title>物理学家发现控制平带量子材料的电子代理</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/physicists-find-electronic-agents-that-govern-flat-band-quantum-materials</link><description>物理学家已经直接可视化了平带量子材料的基本电子构件，这是一类电子运动被有效抑制且强相互作用产生物质涌现相的系统。在一项研究中&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/physicists-find-electronic-agents-that-govern-flat-band-quantum-materials.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 10:32:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/physicists-find-electronic-agents-that-govern-flat-band-quantum-materials</guid></item></channel></rss>